This kind of seems like something that should be fixed.  It implies we're not building the shared libraries correctly.

```
ERROR: phosphor-ipmi-host-1.0+gitAUTOINC+0e7a8af0e5-r1 do_package_qa: QA Issue: non -dev/-dbg/nativesdk- package phosphor-ipmi-host contains symlink .so '/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libdynamiccmds.so'
non -dev/-dbg/nativesdk- package phosphor-ipmi-host contains symlink .so '/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libipmi20.so'
non -dev/-dbg/nativesdk- package phosphor-ipmi-host contains symlink .so '/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libsysintfcmds.so'
non -dev/-dbg/nativesdk- package phosphor-ipmi-host contains symlink .so '/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libwhitelist.so'
non -dev/-dbg/nativesdk- package phosphor-ipmi-host contains symlink .so '/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libusercmds.so' [dev-so]
```

I have been having trouble building it in a way for this to work properly.

I have the same synkink as before, but I guess autotool disable `dev-so` or something.

```
$ ls -l ./tmp/work/armv7a-openbmc-linux-gnueabi/phosphor-ipmi-host/1.0+gitAUTOINC+0e7a8af0e5-r1/package/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libwhitelist.so
lrwxrwxrwx 1 wltu primarygroup 17 Jun 15 19:57 ./tmp/work/armv7a-openbmc-linux-gnueabi/phosphor-ipmi-host/1.0+gitAUTOINC+0e7a8af0e5-r1/package/usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libwhitelist.so -> libwhitelist.so.0
```

Currently,
```
ls -l /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libwhitelist.so.0
lrwxrwxrwx    1 root     root            21 Apr  5  2011 /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libwhitelist.so.0 -> libwhitelist.so.0.0.0
```

----

So I guess it needs to be `ibwhitelist.so.0` instead. um.

actually, I think 

```
  soversion: '0',
```

from https://mesonbuild.com/Build-targets.html#libraries-and-executables should work fine.
nevermind. it doesn't work. I want to see if I can remove `.so`

I suspect there is some combination of a couple changes you’ve made here that are tripping you up.

Notice my comment on line 108 wasn’t to add “.so*” but to add “${SOLIBS}”. If you check the expansion of this variable it will only include the versioned libraries and not the unversioned. Yocto expects that unversioned libraries go into the -dev package, hence this sanity warning. 

We need to:
1. Remove this sanity. 
2. Change below back to SOLIBS. 
3. Maybe add a few FILES:$PN-dev directives. 

It is possible that there were some hacks in the older autotools that didn’t generate the unversioned .so files for the plugin directories. Maybe meson is making them and we need to be explicit about specifying them as well. 

Start with change 1 and 2. I expect after that you’ll get errors along the lines of “there are files installed that didn’t get put in any package” and then it is just 3.  If that isn’t the warning you get, and can’t figure it out, please upload to Gerrit so I can see the failures and I can help from there.

With 1 and 2, I get

```
ERROR: phosphor-ipmi-host-1.0+gitAUTOINC+0e7a8af0e5-r1 do_package: QA Issue: phosphor-ipmi-host: Files/directories were installed but not shipped in any package:
  /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libdynamiccmds.so
  /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libipmi20.so
  /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libsysintfcmds.so
  /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libwhitelist.so
  /usr/lib/ipmid-providers/libusercmds.so
Please set FILES such that these items are packaged. Alternatively if they are unneeded, avoid installing them or delete them within do_install
```

Seems like adding 3 works. um... now I really don't remember why I removed it the first place. Oh well. Seems to work now.

Thanks.
Why did we drop the ${SOLIBS} on all of these?
I guess only .so is in there so it will be the same. I can revert it.
